General Tso's Chickpeas

Sauce:
1 1/2 c water
1/2 c low sodium shoyu
1/4 c hoisin sauce
3 tbsp apricot jam
2 tbsp rice vinegar
2 tbsp cornstarch
1 tbsp grated fresh ginger
1-2 tbsp chili garlic sauce

In a medium bowl, whisk together all ingredients. Taste and add additional garlic chili sauce if more heat desired.

Chickpeas:
15 oz can chickpeas
1 tbsp canola or grapeseed oil
1 large crown of broccoli, cut into florets
2 small red bell peppers, cored and sliced
2 cloves minced garlic
2 green onions, thinly sliced, white and green parts divided
toasted sesame seeds (optional)
brown rice, quinoa, sorghum, or other grain for serving

Drain and rinse the chickpeas, then spread on a paper or dishtowl and pat dry. Set aside. Heat oil in a large, non-stick skillet or wok over medium high. Add the broccoli and bell peppers. Cook 2 min, then stir in the garlic, white parts of green onions, and chickpeas. Cook for 3 more minutes, until the veggies are crisp tender, then pour in the sauce. Bring to a simmer and cook until the sauce thickens, 2 more min. Sprinkl with the green portion of the green onions and sesame seeds. Serve hot with prepared grain.
